00:32:37,722 --> 00:32:40,358
Then we add hot broth and boil everything.

674
00:32:41,893 --> 00:32:44,495
DUMPLING JEONGOL
WITH VARIOUS INGREDIENTS

675
00:32:44,562 --> 00:32:47,966
The color of the ingredients

676
00:32:48,032 --> 00:32:51,102
below the glass lid looks beautiful.

677
00:32:51,169 --> 00:32:53,071
I love that we can continue

678
00:32:53,137 --> 00:32:56,174
to cook the food at the table.

679
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:58,676
-Do you know how jeongol got its name?
-I don't.

680
00:32:58,743 --> 00:33:01,612
The helmets that soldiers used to
wear in the past

681
00:33:01,679 --> 00:33:03,982
were called jeonrip or jeonriptu.

682
00:33:04,048 --> 00:33:05,283
They were made of iron.

683
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:07,151
They flipped them over to cook food.

684
00:33:07,218 --> 00:33:08,853
So they cooked this dish in the helmets.

685
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,822
Gol means "to mix."

686
00:33:10,888 --> 00:33:12,991
So when you combine the two words,
you get jeonriptugol.

687
00:33:13,057 --> 00:33:14,826
Shortened, the word is jeongol.

688
00:33:14,892 --> 00:33:16,027
JEONRIPTUGOL: SOLDIERS
COOKED FOOD IN THEIR HELMETS

689
00:33:17,428 --> 00:33:19,163
That's the origin of the dish.

690
00:33:19,230 --> 00:33:20,131
It's boiling over.

691
00:33:21,165 --> 00:33:25,169
DUMPLING JEONGOL

